HEADWORD: Tincal
<hw>Tin"cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar., Per. & Hind.
<ets>tink⟦amac⟧r</ets>; cf. Malay <ets>tingkal</ets>; all fr. Skr.
<ets><?/a<?/ka<?/a</ets>. Cf. <er>Altincar</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Crude native borax, formerly imported from
Thibet. It was once the chief source of boric compounds. Cf.
<er>Borax</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

